Layman seed entry
<br> <i>also spelled [[civilise]]</i> especially in Britain.

1. To educate or enlighten a person or people to a perceived higher standard of behaviour.

2. To introduce or impose the standards of one [[civilization]] upon another civilization, group or person, arguably with the intent of achieving a perceived higher standard of behaviour.

=== Historical or politically different usage ===
<b>Webster's 1828 Dictionary</b>  To reclaim from a savage state; to introduce civility of manners among a people, and instruct them in the arts of regular life. -